Enumeration Type Documentation

enum ScriptPy::InstanceType

Defines the type of object instance.

Enumerator:
SIT_NONE 

Used when object don't need associated instance (like for built-in types).

SIT_OWNED 

Objects created inside of the script and managed by it.

SIT_SHARED 

Objects returned to the script with lifetime controlled by application.
